      "rationale": "Residual convergence to 1e-5 was achieved for all five baseline operating points and all 18 tolerance-sweep cases. Convergence histories are archived. One CFL-driven restart in case T-14 (VR-03) was resolved by reducing the initial time-step; the restarted case converged fully. No investigation was conducted into whether analogous numerical instabilities at other edge-case operating points could produce silent non-convergence or subtly incorrect hemolysis accumulation without triggering solver termination. Achieved level 2 meets the stated requirement."
